// Tooling typecheck — wired into both `make typecheck` (Makefile:51) and
// release.yml's Typecheck step. Widens the typecheck scope to cover
// load-bearing release-pipeline files that none of the three primary
// tsconfigs reach: scripts/**, bun-build.ts, playwright.config.ts.
//
// Scope (this revision): scripts/ + bun-build.ts + playwright.config.ts.
// tests/** is intentionally excluded — see the deferral note below.
//
// Why a separate tsconfig: extending tsconfig.json's include would force
// noEmit/rootDir gymnastics onto the existing server/desktop emit path.
// A dedicated noEmit config keeps the three primary projects' rootDir
// semantics clean.
//
// Deferred follow-up — tests/** typecheck:
//   tests/** is NOT covered by this gate. Surfacing those errors was
//   outside the cluster-06 budget (the dominant contributor was
//   tests/unit/client/xterm-adapter.test.ts, where adapter test fakes
//   have drifted from current xterm.js types — ~18 errors alone). The
//   remaining test-side errors are mostly fixture-shape drift
//   (HttpHandlerOptions.tmuxControl, DropStorage.autoUnlinkOnClose,
//   RouterState.currentSession) plus a handful of unit-test type
//   regressions. See docs/code-analysis/2026-04-26/clusters/06-ci-and-release-improvements.md
//   for the cluster context. The orchestrator will track follow-up via a
//   docs/ideas note (TODO: filed by orchestrator).
//
// To run manually:   bun x tsc --noEmit -p tsconfig.tooling.json
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "rootDir": ".",
    "noEmit": true,
    "types": ["node", "bun"],
    "lib": ["ES2022", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"],
    "allowImportingTsExtensions": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true
  },
  "include": [
    "scripts/**/*.ts",
    "bun-build.ts",
    "playwright.config.ts"
  ],
  "exclude": ["node_modules", "dist", "vendor", "tests"]
}
